Some Asgard ships come and saves the day at the end and it appears that information gained from the events of Menace seem to be helping (although I haven't seen that episode yet, so I can't say).

As for Heimdell, he is voiced by Teryl Rothery (yeah!) and is a scientist working with a preserved earlier version of the Asgard to find out how to save the race from extinction (turns out, they only reproduce for cloning and haven't been able to sexually reproduce in a thousand years).

Thor had a device inserted into his brain that linked his brain (through the device) to Osiris' and Anubis' computer systems. The Asgard managed to remove the device, but Thor then slipped into a coma. And that is where we were left off in terms of the Asgards.

Oh, yeah, and the Anubis' and Osiris' shields are now strong enough to be unaffected by Asgard weapons fire.
